<h2 class="bold font-l">Harry Potter - Weasley's Wares</h2>
<p class="_pmvv-vidbox-descTxt">
For God knows what reason, the Harry Potter video games use Bertie Bott's Every Flavor Beans as money at Hogwarts instead of the standard wizarding currency Knuts, Sickles, and Galleons. </p>
<p class='example_row'>Example of:<br><a href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WeirdCurrency" class='trope-example-link'>Weird Currency</a></p>
</div>
<div class="video-examples-thumbs">
<a href="#video-link" data-video-id="272y4a" data-video-descrip="In the PC version of Harry Potter and the Chamber of Secrets video game, if Gryffindor got first place in the weekly House Point Ceremony, Harry would get to visit the Bean Bonus Room and collect Bertie Bott's Every Flavor Beans." data-video-title="Harry Potter: Bonus Bean Room" data-video-url="https://d1w6li7s85ibls.cloudfront.net/qvbr/272y4a_640x360p_qvbr.mp4" data-video-thumbnail="https://static.tvtropes.org/trope_videos_transcoded/images/sd/bean_bonus_room.jpg" data-video-trope="Main/BonusStage" data-video-tropename="Bonus Stage" data-video-approval="APPROVED" data-video-troper-rating="" data-video-average-rating="" data-video-rating-count="" data-video-media-sources="Literature/HarryPotterAndTheChamberOfSecrets,VideoGame/HarryPotter,Franchise/HarryPotter" class="video-launch-link video-overlay-link video-background-image lazy-image" data-src="https://static.tvtropes.org/trope_videos_transcoded/images/sd/bean_bonus_room.jpg">
<p><span class="bold">Harry Potter: B...</span></p>
</a>
</div>
